CHRIS BARBER
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    One of the giants of British popular music died on Tuesday 2nd
    March 2021 aged 90. Without his influence and encouragement,
    Britain would not have found its enthusiasm for skiffle, jazz and
    the blues. Without him, pivotal artists like Big Bill Broonzy,
    Sister Rosetta Tharpe, Sonny Terry & Brownie McGhee and Muddy
    Waters would not be recognised today.

